abstract: Moderate Tunisian Islamist party Ennahda wins 41 percent plurality in the country's first free elections, which are also the first elections to occur in the wake of the Arab Spring uprisings.
snippet: Election officials said Thursday that the Islamist Ennahda party won Tunisia’s first free elections, setting it up to form the first Islamist-led government in the wake of the Arab Spring uprisings.
